

To build U-Boot in a standalone environement, perform the  
following actions in the root folder of U-Boot sources : 

1) ./ltib -m prep -p u-boot 
2) cd rpm/BUILD/u-boot-(version) 

3) 
make ARCH=arm
CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/freescale/usr/local/gcc-4.6.2-glibc-2.13-linaro-multilib-2011.12/fsl-
linaro-toolchain/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- distclean

make ARCH=arm
CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/freescale/usr/local/gcc-4.6.2-glibc-2.13-linaro-multilib-2011.12/fsl-
linaro-toolchain/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- mx6sl_evk_config

make ARCH=arm
CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/freescale/usr/local/gcc-4.6.2-glibc-2.13-linaro-multilib-2011.12/fsl-
linaro-toolchain/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi-

To build the kernel in the standalone environement, do the following . 


cd <ltib folder>/rpm/BUILD/linux
make ARCH=arm
CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/freescale/usr/local/gcc-4.6.2-glibc-2.13-linaro-multilib-2011.12/fsl-
linaro-toolchain/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- imx6s_defconfig
make ARCH=arm
CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/freescale/usr/local/gcc-4.6.2-glibc-2.13-linaro-multilib-2011.12/fsl-
linaro-toolchain/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- uImage
